{{Multiple issues|{{notability|date=April 2018}}{{sources|date=April 2018}}}}
'''David McKeon''' is a [[referee]] from [[Ireland]]. He has been a referee for multiple [[U21 Premier League|U21]] and [[U18 Premier League|U19]] qualifying matches, as well as for many games in the [[Irish Football League|Irish football league]].
==Matches refereed==
Dave McKeon has officiated in some major matches. He refereed the [[2007 FAI Cup Final|2007 FAI cup final]] in 2007, and in 2006 was the 4th official in the [[Football Association of Ireland|FAI final]], which was the last football match at [[Lansdowne Road]]. He has also refereed at qualifiers for [[2009 European Under-21Football Championship|Euro 09 U21]], Euro 09 U17, the [[UEFA cup]], Euro 07 U19 and [[2007 European Under-17 Football Championship (qualification)|Euro 07 U21]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.worldfootball.net/referee_summary/david-mckeon/|title=David McKeon - Matches as referee|website=worldfootball.net|language=en-GB|access-date=2018-04-14}}</ref> He has also officiated in the [[Intertoto Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.footballdatabase.eu/football.arbitres.david.mckeon.1437.en.html|title=Football : Referee Page : David McKeon|website=www.footballdatabase.eu|access-date=2018-04-14}}</ref>
==Monday night football==
In March 2008, McKeon allowed ''[[Monday Night Soccer]]'' (the highlights program for the [[League of Ireland]]) to film his entire pre-match routine.
