{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = John Player Ground | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[Nottingham]], [[Nottinghamshire]] | establishment = 1955 <small>(first recorded match)</small> | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1970-1973 | club1 = [[Nottinghamshire County Cricket Club|Nottinghamshire]] | date = 31 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/662.html Ground profile }}
'''John Player Ground''' was a [[cricket]] ground in [[Nottingham]], [[Nottinghamshire]]. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1955, when the Midlands and East of England Women played the North and West of England Women.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/662_misc.html Other matches played on John Player Ground]</ref>
The ground held its first [[List-A cricket|List-A]] match in 1970 when [[Nottinghamshire County Cricket Club|Nottinghamshire]] played [[Hampshire County Cricket Club|Hampshire]] in the [[John Player League]]. Between 1970 and 1973, the ground held 4 List-A matches, the last of which saw Nottinghamshire play [[Gloucestershire County Cricket Club|Gloucestershire]] in the 1973 John Player League.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/662_a.html List-A Matches played on John Player Ground]</ref>
The ground has also held a number of Nottinghamshire Second XI matches in the [[Minor Counties Championship]] and [[Second XI Championship]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/662_minc.html Minor Counties Championship Matches played on John Player Ground]</ref><ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/662_sec.html Second XI Championship Matches played on John Player Ground]</ref>
The ground has also held 3 [[Women's One Day International cricket|Women's One Day Internationals]], the first of which came in 1990 when [[England women's cricket team|England women]] played [[Denmark women's cricket team|Denmark women]]. During the same year, the ground held a second Women's ODI when [[Ireland women's cricket team|Ireland women]] played the [[Netherlands women's cricket team|Netherlands women]]. The final Women's ODI came in the [[1993 Women's Cricket World Cup]] and saw [[India women's cricket team|India women]] played [[West Indies women's cricket team|West Indies women]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/662_wo.html Women's One-Day International Matches played on John Player Ground]</ref>
Today the ground has been developed and is now covered by a leisure centre.
