{{infobox country at games | NOC = KUW | NOCname = [[Kuwait Olympic Committee]] | games = Olympics | year = | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = {{url|www.kuwaitolympic.net }}&nbsp;{{ar icon}} {{en icon}} | location = | competitors = | sports = | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 2 | officials = | appearances = | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = {{Team appearances list|team=Kuwait|competition=Summer Olympics|begin_year=|end_year= }} | winterappearances = | seealso = {{flagIOC|IOA|2016 Summer}} (2016) }}
'''[[Kuwait]]''' has competed in 12 [[Summer Olympic Games|Summer Games]]. To date, Kuwait has won two bronze [[Olympic medal]]s and the Kuwaiti shooter [[Fehaid Al-Deehani]] won a gold medal as an [[Independent Olympic Athletes at the 2016 Summer Olympics|independent athlete]].
In the [[1992 Summer Olympics|1992 Barcelona Games]], Kuwait received a bronze medal in the then-[[demonstration sport]] of [[taekwondo]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Al-Ahram Weekly On-line |title=Three for the Arabs |url=http://weekly.ahram.org.eg/2000/501/sp1.htm |date=28 Sep – 4 Oct 2000 |accessdate=2011-08-08 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110404173239/http://weekly.ahram.org.eg/2000/501/sp1.htm |archivedate=2011-04-04 |df= }}</ref> Their first Olympic medal was a bronze for [[Shooting at the 2000 Summer Olympics – Men's double trap|double trap shooting]], won by [[Fehaid Al-Deehani]] at the [[2000 Olympics]] in [[Sydney, Australia|Sydney]]. Their second was also a bronze won by Al-Deehani in the [[Shooting at the 2012 Summer Olympics – Men's trap|men's trap]] at the [[2012 Summer Olympics]] in [[London]]. In 2016, Al-Deehani won the gold medal for [[Shooting at the 2016 Summer Olympics – Men's double trap|men's double trap]] as an [[Independent Olympic Athletes at the 2016 Summer Olympics|independent athlete]].
The National Olympic Committee for Kuwait was formed in 1957. It was recognized by the [[International Olympic Committee]] in 1966, but has been suspended twice in the past ten years. Due to its most recent suspension, Kuwait was not allowed to compete as a sovereign state at the [[2016 Summer Olympics]], though the nation's participants were able to compete as [[Independent Olympic Athletes]] under the Olympic flag.
