The '''Pakistan Army F.C.''' are a [[Pakistan]]i football club who play in the [[Pakistan Premier League]]. They competed in the [[2016 PFF Cup]].
In the 2006/7 season, keeper Behram Khan set a new Pakistani record by remaining unbeaten for 1170 minutes.
The Pakistan Army represented Pakistan in the [[AFC President's Cup 2006]], and again [[AFC President's Cup 2007|2007]] as last seasons national champions. In both instances, Army showed poor performances, finishing bottom of their groups and failing to qualify for the next rounds of the tournaments. In 2016, [[Pakistan Army FC]] defeated [[PIA FC]] in the [[All-Pakistan Football Tournament]] at the Peoples Football Stadium in Karachi. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/1070841/rangers-all-pakistan-football-tournament-rehman-hasnain-guide-army-to-title/|title=Rangers All-Pakistan Football Tournament: Rehman, Hasnain guide Army to title – The Express Tribune|author=|date=22 March 2016|website=tribune.com.pk|accessdate=12 November 2018}}</ref>
