{{National rugby union | unionname = Cuyo Rugby Union | nativename = Unión de Rugby de Cuyo | logo = | logosize = | founded = {{Start date and age|1945}} | ground = | region = [[Argentine Rugby Union|UAR]] | regionyear = ? | headquarters = [[Mendoza, Argentina|Mendoza]] | president = Ricardo Ragazzone <ref>[http://www.rugbytime.com/noticia.php?id=35997 "Ricardo Ragazzone es el nuevo presidente de la Unión de Cuyo " 26 Dec 2012]</ref> | coach = | womenscoach = | sevenscoach = | countryflag = Argentina | url = [http://www.unionderugbydecuyo.com.ar/clubes.html unionderugbydecuyo.com.ar] }}
The '''Cuyo Rugby Union''' ({{lang-es|'''Unión de Rugby de Cuyo'''}}) (also known for its initials '''URC''') is the organisational body that rules the game of [[rugby union]] in [[Mendoza Province]], Argentina.
== History == It was founded in September 1945 and initially was the governing body of rugby also in the [[San Juan Province, Argentina|San Juan Province]] until the founding of [[Unión Sanjuanina de Rugby]] in September 1952 <ref>{{es}} [http://www.sanjuaninaderugby.com.ar/v2/index.php/historia/ USR Historia]</ref>
== Provincial team ==
The Unión de Rugby de Cuyo is represented in the [[Campeonato Argentino]], a competition in which each of the 24 unions that make up the [[Unión Argentina de Rugby]] (UAR) participate.
=== Titles === *'''[[Campeonato Argentino]]: 1''' :: 2004
